<h2>Sea Bass</h2>

<div>
	<h3>Ingredients</h3>

	<ul>
		<li>One whole sea bass, gutted and filleted</li>
		<li>2 cloves of garlic, crushed</li>
		<li>1 tbsp fresh ginger, grated</li>
		<li>1 bunch spring onions, chopped lengthwise</li>
		<li>Juice of one lemon</li>
		<li>1 tbsp reduced-salt soy sauce</li>
		<li>4 portions boiled rice</li>
		<li>4 portions steamed Chinese sprouting broccoli</li>
	</ul>
</div>

<div>
	<h3>Method</h3>

	<ul>
		<li>Place your filleted sea bass on a sheet of tin foil. Cover with the garlic, grated ginger, spring onions, lemon and soy sauce and wrap into a parcel with tin foil</li>
		<li>Bake for 20mins at 180Â°C</li>
		<li>Serve with boiled rice and steamed Chinese sprouting broccoli</li>
	</ul>
</div>